                                    <p style="margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
                                        Researchers found that interaction patterns are &quot;short-circuiting&quot; memory retention, leading to what is being called <span style="color: #000000;">&quot;Digital Cognitive Erosion.&quot;</span>
                                    </p>
                                    <p style="margin: 0 0 25px 0;">
                                        However, a counter-discovery in Palo Alto offers a lifeline. A 21-day trial using a specific &quot;blue fruit&quot; showed a near-total reversal of cognitive fog.
                                    </p>
